The contestants were divided in two groups. One group with seven castaways were marooned on the beach to start building the camp, while the other group, with the remaining eleven castaways were marooned at the desert, would get crates with items for the camp life. They would reunite later at Day 1. At Day 1, before reuniting with the other group, the group of eleven castaways were instructed to vote for the two members they think was the weakest of the group. The two members voted as the weakest were taken away from the group to the Exile Island. Later that day, they were sent to meet the other contestants, were they would chose the tribes with a Schoolyard Pick.
Two tribes, one of nine celebrities and one of ten non-celebrities ("plebs")

The cast is composed of 18 players, initially split into two tribes containing nine members each. A third tribe was introduced at the first tribe swap. Another tribe swap happened at a double tribal council, where two members from each tribe got swapped to the other tribe in attendance.
